de.tudarmstadt.ukp.clarin.webanno.brat.display.model

Class EntityType

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.tudarmstadt.ukp.clarin.webanno.brat.display.model.EntityType

  • public class EntityType
extends Object
    Different attributes of an Entity used for its visualisation formats. It looks like {"name":"Named Entity","type":"Named Entity","unused":true,"fgColor":"black","bgColor":"cyan", "borderColor":"green","labels":[], "children":[{"name":"LOC","type":"LOC","unused":false, "fgColor":"black","bgColor":"cyan","borderColor":"green","labels":["LOC"],"children":[], "attributes":[],"arcs":[]},....
    Author:
    Seid Muhie Yimam, Richard Eckart de Castilho

        Parameters:
        aName - the "name" (the UIMA type name).
        aLabel - the "label" which is displayed to the user e.g. in the comment popup (the display name)
        aType - the "type" (brat type name, which is basically an identifier used in the UI visual model)
